      <title>WWE SummerSlam 2026: Sunday</title>
      <link>https://www.themoviedb.org/movie/1298510</link>
      <description>&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; max-width: 700px; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div style='margin-bottom: 24px;'&gt;&lt;div style='display: inline-block; background: #f5f5f5; padding: 6px 12px; border-radius: 4px; margin-right: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 14px;'&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Release:&lt;/strong&gt; April 24, 2026&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div style=&quot;margin-top: 24px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;&quot;&gt;
            The 2026 SummerSlam, also promoted as SummerSlam: Minneapolis is an upcoming professional wrestling event produced by WWE. It will be the 39th annual SummerSlam and is scheduled to take place as a two-night event on August 1 and 2, 2026, at U.S. Bank Stadium in Minneapolis, Minnesota. The event will air via pay-per-view (PPV) and livestreaming and will be held for wrestlers from the promotion&amp;#x27;s Raw and SmackDown brand divisions. This will be the first SummerSlam to take place across two nights the first WWE stadium event held in Minneapolis, and the second SummerSlam overall in the city, after the 1999 event, which took place at Target Center.
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;</description>
